---
import Base from '@theme/layouts/Base.astro';
import Sidebar from '@theme/components/Sidebar.astro';
---

<Base title="Editorial Guidelines" description="How we research, write, and maintain every article on this site.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <header class="page-hero">
    <h1>EDITORIAL GUIDELINES</h1>
    <p class="eg-updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>
  </header>

  <!-- Intro blockquote -->
  <div class="eg-intro">
    <blockquote class="lead-quote">
      <p>"At Handy Recovery Advisor, our commitment to accuracy and transparency drives every article we publish. We believe that honest, well-researched content is the foundation of trust."</p>
      <cite>— John Doe, Editor-in-Chief</cite>
    </blockquote>
  </div>

  <!-- Two-column layout -->
  <div class="two-col eg-layout">

    <div class="eg-main">

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section id="introduction">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>

        <h3>Our Mission</h3>
        <p>We exist to help people recover their lost data with confidence. Every recommendation we make is grounded in real testing and genuine expertise. We never promote a product we wouldn't use ourselves.</p>

        <h3>Our Authors</h3>
        <p>Our team consists of experienced tech writers, certified data recovery specialists, and software engineers. Each author brings hands-on knowledge and a passion for helping readers solve real-world problems.</p>

        <h3>Brand Voice</h3>
        <p>We write in a clear, approachable, and authoritative tone. Technical jargon is explained when used, and every article aims to be understood by both beginners and advanced users alike.</p>

        <h3>Content Standards</h3>
        <p>Every piece of content on our site must meet the following standards before publication:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Accuracy</strong> — All claims are verified against primary sources, official documentation, or first-hand testing.</li>
          <li><strong>Clarity</strong> — Instructions are step-by-step and written for non-technical readers.</li>
          <li><strong>Completeness</strong> — We cover the topic thoroughly, including edge cases, limitations, and alternatives.</li>
          <li><strong>Timeliness</strong> — Software versions, pricing, and features are kept up-to-date.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Content Creation Process -->
      <section id="content-creation">
        <h2>Content Creation Process</h2>

        <h3>Types of Content</h3>
        <p>We publish four primary types of content, each following its own rigorous process:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Reviews</strong> — In-depth evaluations of data recovery software based on hands-on testing across multiple platforms and scenarios.</li>
          <li><strong>Guides</strong> — Step-by-step walkthroughs that help readers readers solve specific data loss situations.</li>
          <li><strong>Tutorials</strong> — Practical how-to articles focused on using specific tools and features effectively.</li>
          <li><strong>Comparisons</strong> — Side-by-side analyses of competing products, evaluated against our standardized criteria.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Testing Process</h3>
        <p>We install, configure, and run every tool we review on real hardware. Test scenarios include recovering deleted files, formatted drives, corrupted partitions, and more. Results are documented with screenshots and measurable success rates.</p>

        <blockquote class="team-quote">
          <p>"We never rely solely on marketing materials. If we can't test it ourselves, we won't review it."</p>
          <cite>— Jane Smith, Lead Reviewer</cite>
        </blockquote>

        <h3>Crafting Articles</h3>
        <p>After testing is complete, our writers draft articles following a standardized outline. Each article includes an introduction, methodology, findings, pros/cons, and a clear verdict. We aim for readability without sacrificing depth.</p>

        <h3>Review and QA</h3>
        <p>Before publication, every article passes through a multi-stage quality assurance process. This includes technical accuracy checks, grammar editing, SEO optimization, and a final editorial review.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Fact-Checking Policy -->
      <section id="fact-checking">
        <h2>Fact-Checking Policy</h2>
        <p>Our editorial team follows a three-step fact-checking process to ensure every published article meets our accuracy standards:</p>

        <div class="eg-steps">
          <div class="eg-step">
            <span class="eg-step-num">1</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Author Verification</h3>
              <p>The writer tests the software or procedure first-hand and documents results with screenshots and measurable data. All statistics and claims are cross-referenced with official sources.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="eg-step">
            <span class="eg-step-num">2</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Peer Review</h3>
              <p>A second team member independently verifies key claims and checks for bias, omissions, or outdated information. They also evaluate the article's structure and readability.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="eg-step">
            <span class="eg-step-num">3</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Final Edit</h3>
              <p>The editor-in-chief reviews the article for completeness, accuracy, and tone before publication. Any remaining issues are resolved before the article goes live.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Corrections Policy -->
      <section id="corrections">
        <h2>Corrections Policy</h2>
        <p>We take errors seriously. If you find inaccurate information in any of our articles, here's how we handle corrections:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Reporting Errors</strong> — Readers can report issues via our contact form or by emailing our editorial team directly. We acknowledge all reports within 48 hours.</li>
          <li><strong>Minor Corrections</strong> — Typos, broken links, and small factual updates are fixed immediately without a formal notice.</li>
          <li><strong>Major Corrections</strong> — Significant factual errors are corrected and noted with a visible correction notice at the top of the article.</li>
          <li><strong>Update Frequency</strong> — Every review is re-tested at least once every 12 months. Major software updates trigger an immediate re-review.</li>
        </ul>

        <blockquote class="team-quote">
          <p>"Getting it right matters more than getting it first. When we make a mistake, we own it and fix it fast."</p>
          <cite>— Alex Chen, Managing Editor</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

      <!-- How We Rate Software -->
      <section id="ratings">
        <h2>How We Rate Software</h2>
        <p>Our ratings are based on a weighted scoring system that evaluates five key areas. Each product is tested under identical conditions to ensure fair and consistent comparisons:</p>

        <div class="eg-rating-table">
          <div class="eg-rating-row">
            <span class="eg-rating-label">Recovery Success Rate</span>
            <div class="eg-rating-bar">
              <div class="eg-rating-fill" style="width: 40%"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="eg-rating-pct">40%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="eg-rating-row">
            <span class="eg-rating-label">Ease of Use</span>
            <div class="eg-rating-bar">
              <div class="eg-rating-fill" style="width: 20%"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="eg-rating-pct">20%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="eg-rating-row">
            <span class="eg-rating-label">Features &amp; Compatibility</span>
            <div class="eg-rating-bar">
              <div class="eg-rating-fill" style="width: 20%"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="eg-rating-pct">20%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="eg-rating-row">
            <span class="eg-rating-label">Pricing &amp; Value</span>
            <div class="eg-rating-bar">
              <div class="eg-rating-fill" style="width: 10%"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="eg-rating-pct">10%</span>
          </div>
          <div class="eg-rating-row">
            <span class="eg-rating-label">Customer Support</span>
            <div class="eg-rating-bar">
              <div class="eg-rating-fill" style="width: 10%"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="eg-rating-pct">10%</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Affiliate Disclosure -->
      <section id="affiliate">
        <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
        <blockquote class="disclosure-quote">
          <p>Some links on this site are affiliate links. This means we may earn a small commission if you purchase through our link — at no extra cost to you. Affiliate relationships never influence our ratings or recommendations.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <p>We clearly label sponsored content and maintain a strict separation between editorial and advertising. Our reviews are based solely on hands-on testing and objective criteria. We will never promote a product in exchange for payment, and our editorial team has full independence over the content we publish.</p>

        <blockquote class="team-quote">
          <p>"Our readers trust us because we put honesty first. That trust is worth more than any commission."</p>
          <cite>— John Doe, Editor-in-Chief</cite>
        </blockquote>
      </section>

    </div>

    <!-- Sidebar -->
    <div class="sidebar">
      <Sidebar />
    </div>

  </div>

</Base>

<style>
  /* ---- Hero date override ---- */
  .eg-updated {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, .6);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Intro wrapper ---- */
  .eg-intro {
    max-width: var(--max-width);
    margin-inline: auto;
    padding-inline: 40px;
  }

  /* ---- Lead Quote ---- */
  .lead-quote {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .lead-quote p {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
  }
  .lead-quote cite {
    display: block;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  /* ---- Two-col vertical spacing ---- */
  .eg-layout {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  /* ---- Main Content ---- */
  .eg-main section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .eg-main section:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  .eg-main h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 0 0 16px;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .eg-main h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin: 24px 0 10px;
  }
  .eg-main p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
  }
  .eg-main ul,
  .eg-main ol {
    padding-left: 24px;
    margin: 0 0 16px;
  }
  .eg-main li {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #374151;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }

  /* ---- Team Quote ---- */
  .team-quote {
    margin: 2rem 0;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #374151;
  }
  .team-quote p {
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .team-quote cite {
    display: block;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  /* ---- Disclosure Quote ---- */
  .disclosure-quote {
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: #fef9e7;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-cta-yellow);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius) var(--radius) 0;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #374151;
  }
  .disclosure-quote p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #374151;
  }

  /* ---- Fact-checking steps ---- */
  .eg-steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 20px;
    margin: 20px 0;
  }
  .eg-step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .eg-step-num {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 16px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }
  .eg-step h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .eg-step p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  /* ---- Rating bars ---- */
  .eg-rating-table {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
    margin: 20px 0;
  }
  .eg-rating-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
  }
  .eg-rating-label {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 200px;
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .eg-rating-bar {
    flex: 1;
    height: 12px;
    background: var(--color-bg-alt);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .eg-rating-fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    border-radius: 6px;
    transition: width 0.3s ease;
  }
  .eg-rating-pct {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 40px;
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  /* ---- Responsive ---- */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .eg-intro {
      padding-inline: 20px;
    }
    .lead-quote {
      margin: 1.5rem 0;
      padding: 1.25rem;
      font-size: 15px;
    }
    .eg-main h2 {
      font-size: 20px;
    }
    .eg-main h3 {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
    .eg-rating-label {
      width: 140px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
    .eg-rating-pct {
      width: 36px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }
  }
</style>
